UTF-8
# Minimal, self-owned fixture for the nocross-precedence unit test in
# src/translator/table/primary.rs. Not derived from any liblouis table --
# it exists purely to give "ere" a hyphenation break between 'e' and 'r'
# ("e-re"), so that a `nocross always er` rule and a `nocross partword re`
# rule compete for the same letters and only one can win depending on
# where the real word's syllable break falls.
LEFTHYPHENMIN 1
RIGHTHYPHENMIN 1
.e1r
